Anogenital region
(

). Genital, aggenital, anal, and adanal setae (9–11) setae setiform, thin, roughened. Adanal lyrifissure distinct. Marginal porose area represented by some band-like parts.

Note: Roman letters refer to normal setae; Greek letters to solenidia (except ε = famulus); single quotation mark (
’
